gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bucks 125, Spurs 121
gameRecap.excerpt: Led by Giannis Antetokounmpo’s 44 points (19-28 FG), 14 rebounds and seven assists, the Bucks defeated the Spurs, 125-121. This is Antetokounmpo’s sixth consecutive game with 25+ points, 10+ rebounds and 5+ assists. Damian Lillard added 25 points and 10 assists for the Bucks in the victory, while Devin Vassell (34 points, six 3PM) and Victor Wembanyama (27 points, nine rebounds) combined for 61 points for the Spurs in the losing effort. The Bucks snap a 2-game losing streak as they improve to 25-10 on the season, while the Spurs fall to 5-29.
